rsonal name <i>Álvaro</i> (see   Alvaro  ). Compare   Alavarez  ,   Albares  ,   Albarez  ,   Alvares  , and   Alverez  .","Jewish (Sephardic): adoption of the name in 1 above at the moment of conversion to Roman Catholicism. After the return to Judaism (generations later), some descendants retained the name their families used as Catholics."],"variants":[{"name":"Alverez","meanings":["(1997: 275;2007: 1656; 2010: NA)","Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Alberto, Alfredo, Francisco, Mario, Miguel, Ramon, Carlos, Javier, Luis, Manuel, Marcelino.","Hispanic (<b>Álverez</b>): altered form of Spanish <b>Álvarez</b> (see   Alvarez  )."]},{"name":"Albares","meanings":["Spanish: variant of <b>Álvarez</b> (see   Alvarez  )."]},{"name":"Alavarez","meanings":["Hispanic: altered form of Spanish <b>Álvarez</b> (see   Alvarez  )."]},{"name":"Alvaro","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Francisco, Raul, Adelaida, Alba, Alberto, Alejandro, Anaya, Benito, Celestino, Chavez, Emilia.  Italian Antonio, Alfonse, Angelo, Cesare, Giuseppe, Rocco, Sal.","Spanish and Portuguese (<b>Álvaro</b>); Italian: from the personal name <i>Álvaro</i>, <i>Alvaro</i>, which is of ancient Germanic (Visigothic) origin, but the exact etymology is not clear."]},{"name":"Albarez","meanings":["Spanish (<b>Álbarez</b>): variant of <b>Álvarez</b> (see   Alvarez  ). This surname is very rare in Spain."]}]},{"name":"María","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name derived from Mapia, one of the Greek forms of Miriam. Maria is found as a male name as well as a female name. Viscount Montague, of Cowdray, Sussex, who succeeded to the title as second viscount, was christened Anthony Maria Browne. In Camden's Remains (p. 44), referred to in Delicie Literarise, occurs Thomas Maria Wingfield; and there was also a Sir Edward Maria Wingfield. The name appears to have been adopted in the latter family from Mary, daughter of Henry VIII. Compare Notes and Queries 5th S. ii. 73, 316, 478. Marie is f